## THOROUGH UI LAYOUT BUG INVESTIGATION: Onboarding vs Chat Message Rendering

I've completed a comprehensive investigation of how the onboarding page and normal chat screen render messages and tool cards. Here's the complete mapping:

### KEY FINDING: CONTAINER WIDTH MISMATCH

The bug is caused by a **width constraint difference** between the two screens:

**Onboarding message container:** `max-w-3xl` (3xl = 48rem = 768px)  
**Normal chat container:** `max-w-(--breakpoint-lg)` (custom CSS variable, typically ~90rem or wider)

When tool cards like `ToolCard` (wrapped around `TextDocumentView`) have `max-w-4xl`, they exceed the onboarding's `max-w-3xl` parent and get cut off.

---

### 1. ONBOARDING PAGE ROUTE & ARCHITECTURE

**File:** `/Users/aryan/Projects/GAIA/gaia-onboarding-revamp/apps/web/src/app/[locale]/(main)/onboarding/page.tsx`

**Page structure (lines 1-180):**
- Uses `useOnboarding` hook with `skipAutoRedirect: true` to keep chat stage rendered locally
- Renders `OnboardingShell` which provides the full-screen layout
- Mounts `MessagesRegion` once to persist transcript across stage transitions
- Stages switch via conditional rendering (`stageContent` and `composer`)

**Key wrapper:** `OnboardingShell` component

---

### 2. MESSAGE RENDERING IN ONBOARDING

#### **MessagesRegion.tsx** — `/Users/aryan/Projects/GAIA/gaia-onboarding-revamp/apps/web/src/features/onboarding/components/MessagesRegion.tsx`

(Lines 1-50)
```tsx
return (
  <OnboardingMessages messages={messages} processingChecklist={checklist} />
);
```
Delegates to `OnboardingMessages`.

#### **OnboardingMessages.tsx** — `/Users/aryan/Projects/GAIA/gaia-onboarding-revamp/apps/web/src/features/onboarding/components/OnboardingMessages.tsx`

(Lines 49-105)
```tsx
{messages.map((message, index) => {
  const isLastBot = message.type === "bot" && index === messages.length - 1;
  return (
    <m.div
      key={message.id}
      className="mb-4"  // ← Individual message wrapper, no max-w constraint
      initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 15 }}
      animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
      transition={{...}}
    >
      {message.type === "bot" ? (
        <OnboardingBotBubble text={message.content}>
          {isLastBot && processingChecklist && (
            <m.div className="ml-10.75" {...}>
              {processingChecklist}
            </m.div>
          )}
        </OnboardingBotBubble>
      ) : (
        <div className="flex items-end justify-end gap-0">
          <OnboardingUserBubble text={message.content} />
        </div>
      )}
    </m.div>
  );
})}
```

**KEY ISSUE:** No max-width constraint on the message wrappers here. Width is inherited from parent.

#### **OnboardingShell.tsx** — `/Users/aryan/Projects/GAIA/gaia-onboarding-revamp/apps/web/src/features/onboarding/components/OnboardingShell.tsx`

(Lines 104-133) — **THE CULPRIT**
