    <HoloCardReveal personalizationData={state.server} />
  </div>
</m.div>
```

**Container classes:**
- `"mt-4 space-y-4"` — spacing only, no width constraint
- **Inherits `max-w-3xl` from parent**

---

### SUMMARY OF CONTAINER HIERARCHY

#### **ONBOARDING (BUGGY)**

```
OnboardingShell
  ↓
  <div className="relative z-10 flex-1 overflow-y-auto px-4 pt-20">
    ↓ (scrollable region)
    <div className="relative mx-auto w-full max-w-3xl" {...paddingStyle}>
      ↓ (WIDTH-CONSTRAINED TO 768px)
      MessagesRegion / Chat / RevealTodos
        ↓
        OnboardingMessages / OnboardingChatStream
          ↓
          <m.div className="mb-4">
            ↓
            ChatBubbleBot
              ↓
              ToolCard size="wide" (max-w-4xl = 896px)
              ❌ EXCEEDS PARENT by 128px → OVERFLOW/CUT OFF
```

#### **NORMAL CHAT (WORKS)**

```
ChatPage
  ↓
  ChatWithMessages
    ↓
    <div className="min-h-0 flex-1 overflow-y-auto overscroll-contain">
      ↓ (scrollable region)
      ChatSection
        ↓
        <div className="conversation_history mx-auto w-full max-w-(--breakpoint-lg) ...">
          ↓ (WIDTH-CONSTRAINED TO CSS VAR, ~90rem or wider)
          ChatRenderer
            ↓
            ChatBubbleBot (multiple)
              ↓
              ToolCard size="wide" (max-w-4xl = 896px)
              ✓ FITS within wider parent
```

---

### ROOT CAUSE

The onboarding page's `OnboardingShell` uses `max-w-3xl` (768px), while the normal chat uses `max-w-(--breakpoint-lg)` which is significantly wider. Tool cards rendered inside either flow inherit this constraint, and when a card is sized `wide` (`max-w-4xl` = 896px), it exceeds the onboarding's narrower wrapper.

### RECOMMENDED FIX

Change line 127 in `OnboardingShell.tsx`:

```tsx
// Before:
className="relative mx-auto w-full max-w-3xl"

// After (to match chat width):
className="relative mx-auto w-full max-w-(--breakpoint-lg)"
```

Or increase to at least `max-w-4xl` to accommodate wide tool cards:

```tsx
className="relative mx-auto w-full max-w-4xl"
```

